 :$x \mathrel \RR y \implies y \mathrel \RR x$\nAs $\RR$ is [[Definition:Transitive Relation|transitive]]: 
 :$x \mathrel \RR y \land y \mathrel \RR x \implies x \mathrel \RR x$\nAs $\RR$ is [[Definition:Serial Relation|serial]]: 
 :$\forall x \in S: \exists y \in S: x \mathrel \RR y$\nLet $x \in S$.\nThen 
 {{begin-eqn}} 
